SYNOPSIS
	muffle
	muffle <class> <on>|<off>

DESCRIPTION
	With the muffle command you can suppress different kind of output
	you receive.

	There are two general ways of using the command:

	Without any parameters it prints out your current muffle settings.

	With parameter you can turn the output for the given class on or
        off.

	Currently the following classes are available:
	
	channel : Anything that is written on channels (actually a choff all)
	fun     : Any output of so-called fun-items like voodoo dolls or
                  washing machines with pink feet.

EXAMPLES
	Turn off all channel output:

	muffle channel on

	Turn on the channel output again:

	muffle channel off

SEE ALSO
	chon, choff
	